content:
Navigate to the Overall Performance Tab

In Performance, click Model Evaluation, then click Overall Performance.

Class Selector

Select a class to see its performance statistics.

ROC Curve

Displays the performance measurement for the selected class. ROC is a probability curve and AUC (Area Under the Curve) represents the degree or measure of separability. This chart shows how well the model is able to distinguish between classes.

Y-axis: True Positive Rate
X-axis: False Positive Rate

Model (blue line)
No Model (gray line)—the same as random chance

Row Count for the Selected Class

Number of observations in the training dataset associated with the selected class.

AUC

Measures the model’s rate of correct classification for the selected class.

Confusion Matrix for the Selected Class

Evaluates the trade-offs between different error types for the selected class. It displays how many times the model correctly and incorrectly classifies an observation as true and false for the class.

Key Metrics:

METRIC	DESCRIPTION
F1 Score	
True Positive Rate	
Precision	
Negative Predictive Value	
Markedness	
MCC	
Informedness	
Accuracy	

Confusion Matrix for All Classes

This chart shows you at a glance how accurately the model predicts each class. Where the row and column for each class intersect in the table, the color of the square indicates the model’s accuracy.

True Positive Rate: TPR = TP / (TP + FN)
Precision = TP / (TP + FP)
NPV = TN / (TN + FN)

Range:

0.5 means that the model performed no better than random guessing.
1.0 means that the model correctly classified the data 100% of the time.
title: Evaluating Model Quality in Multiclass Classification
